# TypeScript Frontend Conventions

## Component Structure
- Functional components with hooks
- shadcn/ui for UI components (in `src/components/ui/`)
- Custom components alongside pages or in `src/components/`

## File Organization
```
src/
├── components/     # Reusable components
│   └── ui/         # shadcn/ui primitives (don't modify)
├── hooks/          # Custom React hooks (use*.ts)
├── pages/          # Route pages
├── lib/            # Utilities
│   ├── api.ts      # Backend API client
│   └── utils.ts    # Helper functions
└── types/          # TypeScript type definitions
```

## Naming
- Components: PascalCase (`MealSlotCard.tsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix (`useMealPlans.ts`)
- Utilities: camelCase (`mappers.ts`)

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS for all styling
- Use `cn()` utility for conditional classes
- Avoid inline styles

## State Management
- React hooks for local state
- Custom hooks in `hooks/` for shared logic
- API calls via hooks (e.g., `useFridge`, `useRecipes`)

## API Integration
- API client in `src/lib/api.ts`
- Use React Query patterns via custom hooks
- Handle loading/error states

## TypeScript
- Strict mode enabled
- Define types in `types/` or co-located
- Prefer interfaces for object shapes
- Use discriminated unions for variants

## Testing
- Playwright for e2e tests in `e2e/`
- Test files: `*.spec.ts`
- Fixtures in `e2e/fixtures/`
